      • removeDuplicates

        private void removeDuplicates(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> orLines)
        This function takes in an arraylist and checks for duplicates against validLines. If there is a duplicate entry, it is removed from validLines. After this process, all of the given arraylist's contents are added to validLines.
        Parameters:
        orLines - This is an arraylist that is checked against validLines for duplicate error entries

      • addLines

        protected void addLines(java.lang.String line,
                        java.io.BufferedReader br)
                 throws java.io.IOException
        This function adds lines to validLines, deadlockOrLines, and arrowOrLines depending on the logical statement that the user has inputed. Lines that fit the statement will be put into the above arraylists while invalid lines will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        line - is a string containing the first line to be read
        br - is a BufferedReader that parses through the lines of the log file
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there is an error with the BufferedReader

      • addORs

        protected void addORs()
        This function looks at the logical statement that the user has given and checks for special cases (such as AND NOT DEADLOCK, AND NOT ARROW and sees if an OR operand was set. If so, then the variable orWord is set as the corresponding word.

      • progressArrowBr

        private java.lang.String progressArrowBr(java.io.BufferedReader logbr,
                                         java.lang.String line)
                                  throws java.io.IOException
        This function progresses the buffered reader if the user has indicated that they do NOT want to include any arrow errors. If there is a single arrow (indicated by a time stamp dif) then the function will return the line right below the first arrow found. Otherwise if there are matching arrows, the line returned will be the line below the matching arrow.
        Parameters:
        logbr - A buffered reader to advance through the file, same br from LogParser
        line - The file line where an arrow was found
        Returns:
        Returns a string that gives the program a new place to parse through
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there is an error with the BufferedReader

      • progressDeadlockBr

        private java.lang.String progressDeadlockBr(java.io.BufferedReader logbr,
                                            java.lang.String line)
                                     throws java.io.IOException
        This function progresses the buffered reader if the user has indicated that they do NOT want to include any DEADLOCK errors. If there is a single DEADLOCK (indicated by a time stamp dif) then the function will return the line right below the first DEADLOCK found. Otherwise if there are matching DEADLOCKs, the line returned will be the line below the matching DEADLOCK.
        Parameters:
        logbr - A buffered reader to advance through the file, same br from LogParser
        line - The file line where a DEADLOCK was found
        Returns:
        Returns a string that gives the program a new place to parse through
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there is an error with the BufferedReader

      • makeDeadlockLine

        private java.lang.String makeDeadlockLine(java.io.BufferedReader logbr,
                                          java.lang.String line)
                                   throws java.io.IOException
        This function generates a string that returns the entire deadlock error, which includes the first line where a deadlock was found, and then the subsequent lines in between the matching deadlock. If the error is a single error occurrence, then the error message is simply "".
        Parameters:
        logbr - Buffered Reader to read through file, same br from LogParser
        line - The fileline where DEADLOCK first occurred
        Returns:
        Returns a string with the full DEADLOCK error
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there is an error with the BufferedReader

      • makeArrowLine

        private java.lang.String makeArrowLine(java.io.BufferedReader logbr,
                                       java.lang.String logLine,
                                       java.lang.String[] currArray)
                                throws java.io.IOException
        This function generates the entire line of an arrow error, and includes all the lines between the first arrow and then the matching arrow error. The string returned includes the first line where the arrow was found and the full error message, but not the line including the matching arrow. If there is only a single arrow, then only the first line is returned.
        Parameters:
        logbr - Buffered Reader to read through file, same br from LogParser
        logLine - Fileline where an arrow error was first found
        currArray - The same line as above but split into an array using split(" ")
        Returns:
        Returns a string with the full arrow error
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If there is a problem reading with the bufferedReader
